Closing Statement

ORL is published to explore the possibility that ledger correctness can emerge from structure rather than from time, order, or synchronization.

The project is released openly to encourage independent research, validation, and implementation of structure-based ledger models.

Ledger systems, long governed by sequencing and timing, may also be understood as processes of structural validation.

ORL is offered as a reference model for that exploration.
